The defendant Donna M. Ciaffarafa was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Donna M. Ciaffarafa in court.  Kristi S. Tlusty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Plea agreement put into the record.  Court advises defendant of right to an attorney. Court finds defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waives right to an attorney.  Defendant enters a plea of  no contest.   Plea colloquy.  Plea freely, voluntarily and intelligently; factual basis exists.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Court orders court costs; DNA sample and surcharge; letter of apology to Deputy Schuett to be done by the end of today and preapproved by the victim witness coordinator.  The costs are to be added to defendants current payment plan of $50.00 a month with payments increasing to $75.00 a month in March.  Appeal rights given to defendant.  - rt
